-- ============================================================
-- Related specs
-- ============================================================

-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium
--   The companion spec at the layout layer. PerStreamAllocator,
--   MaskPerStream, PerStreamDispatch contracts live there; THIS
--   spec extends their per-stream-isolation guarantees from
--   write-side + dispatch-side to read-side. The write-side
--   patching is already shipped (PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D N2.b); the
--   read-side patching is Tier 2 of PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md.
--
-- specs/graphs/cuda_graph_reuse.allium
--   The CUDA backend's cache mechanism. Its
--   ViewCpyAddressTolerance contract (ViewCpySrcAddressMismatch-
--   ToleratedOnVcpy invariant) is the mechanism this spec's
--   ReadViewIsLegitimateVIEW depends on. The two specs are
--   independent: dropping the libllama bailout (this spec's
--   load-bearing change) does not change any contract in
--   cuda_graph_reuse.allium.
--
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium
--   The scheduler-level Bug C closure. Under per-stream
--   dispatch (still the dispatch model under Tier 2),
--   MixedBatchProhibition holds at the batch boundary; this
--   spec lifts the same property to the read-view boundary.
--   Together they make Bug C absent at every layer the decode
--   path touches.
--
-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium (forthcoming,
-- P0.B.S1.c)
--   The Tier 3 unified-dispatch contract. Under unified
--   dispatch, the read view's shape changes from
--   [head_dim, n_kv, n_head_kv] to
--   [head_dim, n_kv_per_stream, n_head_kv, n_stream]; the
--   per-stream offset patch then collapses into ne[3]-aware
--   FA dispatch (PSKV already handles this). The Tier 2
--   contracts above are STRICTLY WEAKER than the Tier 3
--   contracts; Tier 3 is permitted to subsume them.
